ContainedObjects.LuaScript:
local side , text , plr = '' , '' , 'Black'
local timesRolled , randomized = 0 , false

function onObjectRandomize( Object , player_color )
 if Object.getGUID() == self.getGUID() then
  if player_color ~= plr then
   changePlayer(player_color)
  end
  if not randomized then
   randomized = true
   startLuaCoroutine(self, 'whileDrop')
  end
 end
end

function whileDrop()
 while not self.resting do
  coroutine.yield(0) -- Always yield 0 to resume
 end
 randomized = false
 printDiceFace()
 coroutine.yield(1) -- Yield anything other than 0 to break out
end

function printDiceFace()
 local value = self.getValue()
 --You can customize the message per Value
 if value == 1 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got tails!'
 elseif value == 2 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got heads!'
 else
 --Or Remove the If block to make a generic message about what value they rolled
  side = ' made noise in corridor '..value
 end
 text = plr..side
 printToAll(text, self.getColorTint())
 --For if you need to know how many times a player has rolled the dice (optional)
 timesRolled = timesRolled + 1
end

function changePlayer(new)
 plr = new
 timesRolled = 0
 --This changes the color of the Dice to whom ever rolled it
 local rgb = stringColorToRGB(plr)
 local color = {rgb["r"], rgb["g"], rgb["b"]}
end

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.LuaScript:
MIN_VALUE = 0
MAX_VALUE = 99

function updateSave()
    local data_to_save = {value1, value2}
    saved_data = JSON.encode(data_to_save)
    self.script_state = saved_data
end


function onLoad(saved_data)
    if saved_data ~= "" then
        local loaded_data = JSON.decode(saved_data)
        --Set up information off of loaded_data
        value1 = loaded_data[1]
        value2 = loaded_data[2]
    else
        --Set up information for if there is no saved saved data
        value1 = 0
        value2 = 0
    end

    createBtns()
end


--Beginning Setup


--Make setup button
function createBtns()
	local pos = {-0.7,0.1,0}
    local pos2 = {1.4,0.1,0}    -- position à ajuster
	local rot = {0,0,0}
	local h = 250
	local w = 250
	local f_size = 150
	local f_color = {1,1,1,255}
	local bg_color = {0,0,0,0}
	local diff = 0.8
	
	--center display
	self.createButton({
        label=tostring(value1),
        click_function="add_subtract",
        function_owner=self,
        position=pos,
        rotation=rot,
        height=h,
        width=w,
        font_size=f_size,
        scale={x=3, y=3, z=3},
        font_color = f_color,
        color = bg_color
    })

    --second display
	self.createButton({
        label=tostring(value2),
        click_function="add_subtract_2",
        function_owner=self,
        position=pos2,
        rotation=rot,
        height=h,
        width=w,
        font_size=f_size,
        scale={x=3, y=3, z=3},
        font_color=f_color, 
        color = bg_color
    })
	
end

local side , text , plr = '' , '' , 'Black'
local timesRolled , randomized = 0 , false

function onObjectRandomize( Object , player_color )
 if Object.getGUID() == self.getGUID() then
  if player_color ~= plr then
   changePlayer(player_color)
  end
  if not randomized then
   randomized = true
   startLuaCoroutine(self, 'whileDrop')
  end
 end
end

function whileDrop()
 while not self.resting do
  coroutine.yield(0) -- Always yield 0 to resume
 end
 randomized = false
 printDiceFace()
 coroutine.yield(1) -- Yield anything other than 0 to break out
end

function printDiceFace()
 local value = self.getValue()
 --You can customize the message per Value
 if value == 1 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got tails!'
 elseif value == 2 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got heads!'
 else
 --Or Remove the If block to make a generic message about what value they rolled
  side = ' made noise in corridor '..value
 end

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Dice
ContainedObjects.LuaScript:
local side , text , plr = '' , '' , 'Black'
local timesRolled , randomized = 0 , false

function onObjectRandomize( Object , player_color )
 if Object.getGUID() == self.getGUID() then
  if player_color ~= plr then
   changePlayer(player_color)
  end
  if not randomized then
   randomized = true
   startLuaCoroutine(self, 'whileDrop')
  end
 end
end

function whileDrop()
 while not self.resting do
  coroutine.yield(0) -- Always yield 0 to resume
 end
 randomized = false
 printDiceFace()
 coroutine.yield(1) -- Yield anything other than 0 to break out
end

function printDiceFace()
 local value = self.getValue()
 --You can customize the message per Value
 if value == 1 then
  side = ' rolled a 1!'
 elseif value == 2 then
  side = ' rolled a 2!'
 elseif value == 3 then
  side = ' rolled a 3!'
 elseif value == 4 then
  side = ' rolled a 4!'
 elseif value == 5 then
  side = ' rolled a 5!'
 elseif value == 6 then
  side = ' rolled a 6!'
 elseif value == 7 then
  side = ' rolled a 7!'
 elseif value == 8 then
  side = ' rolled a 8!'
 elseif value == 9 then
  side = ' rolled a 9!'
 elseif value == 10 then
  side = ' rolled a 10!'
 elseif value == 11 then
  side = ' rolled a 11!'
 elseif value == 12 then
  side = ' rolled a 12!'
 elseif value == 13 then
  side = ' rolled a 13!'
 elseif value == 14 then
  side = ' rolled a 14!'
 elseif value == 15 then
  side = ' rolled a 15!'
 elseif value == 16 then
  side = ' rolled a 16!'
 elseif value == 17 then
  side = ' rolled a 17!'
 elseif value == 18 then
  side = ' rolled a 18!'
 elseif value == 19 then
  side = ' rolled a 19!'
 elseif value == 20 then
  side = ' rolled a 20!'
 else
 --Or Remove the If block to make a generic message about what value they rolled
  side = ' made noise in corridor '..value
 end
 text = plr..side
 printToAll(text, self.getColorTint())
 --For if you need to know how many times a player has rolled the dice (optional)
 timesRolled = timesRolled + 1
end

function changePlayer(new)
 plr = new
 timesRolled = 0
 --This changes the color of the Dice to whom ever rolled it
 local rgb = stringColorToRGB(plr)
 local color = {rgb["r"], rgb["g"], rgb["b"]}
end

ContainedObjects.Name: Card

Whenever chaos ensues, put an indestructible counter on target creature you control that attacked this turn.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card

Sixty-Six Seconds — At the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice a creature with the least toughness among creatures you control. Then investigate.
Whenever chaos ensues, activated abilities of artifact tokens you control cost {2} less to activate this turn.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card

Stormcage Containment Facility
Plane — Unknown Planet 0CMC
ContainedObjects.Description:
Each creature card in your graveyard has escape. The escape cost is equal to the card's mana cost plus exile three other cards from your graveyard. (You may cast cards from your graveyard for their escape cost.)
Whenever chaos ensues, detain target creature an opponent controls. (Until your next turn, that creature can't attack or block and its activated abilities can't be activated.)

ContainedObjects.Name: Card

Plane — Earth 0CMC
ContainedObjects.Description:
Whenever you roll the planar die, creatures you control get +1/+1 and gain haste until end of turn.
Whenever chaos ensues, end the turn. (Exile all spells and abilities from the stack. The player whose turn it is discards down to their maximum hand size. Damage wears off, and "this turn" and "until end of turn" effects end.)

ContainedObjects.Name: Card

The Doctor's Childhood Barn
Plane — Gallifrey 0CMC
ContainedObjects.Description:
Creatures enter tapped.
Whenever chaos ensues, for each opponent, choose up to one target nonland permanent that opponent controls. Untap those permanents. They phase out. They can't phase in for as long as The Doctor's Childhood Barn remains face up. When a player planeswalks, those permanents phase in.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Name: Card

At the beginning of each of your postcombat main phases, there is an additional beginning phase after this phase. (The beginning phase includes the untap, upkeep, and draw steps.)
When chaos ensues, reverse the game's turn order. Then planeswalk. (For example, if play had proceeded clockwise around the table, it now goes counterclockwise.)

MIN_VALUE = 0
MAX_VALUE = 99

function updateSave()
    local data_to_save = {value1, value2}
    saved_data = JSON.encode(data_to_save)
    self.script_state = saved_data
end


function onLoad(saved_data)
    if saved_data ~= "" then
        local loaded_data = JSON.decode(saved_data)
        --Set up information off of loaded_data
        value1 = loaded_data[1]
        value2 = loaded_data[2]
    else
        --Set up information for if there is no saved saved data
        value1 = 0
        value2 = 0
    end

    createBtns()
end


--Beginning Setup


--Make setup button
function createBtns()
	local pos = {-0.7,0.1,0}
    local pos2 = {1.4,0.1,0}    -- position à ajuster
	local rot = {0,0,0}
	local h = 250
	local w = 250
	local f_size = 150
	local f_color = {1,1,1,255}
	local bg_color = {0,0,0,0}
	local diff = 0.8
	
	--center display
	self.createButton({
        label=tostring(value1),
        click_function="add_subtract",
        function_owner=self,
        position=pos,
        rotation=rot,
        height=h,
        width=w,
        font_size=f_size,
        scale={x=3, y=3, z=3},
        font_color = f_color,
        color = bg_color
    })

    --second display
	self.createButton({
        label=tostring(value2),
        click_function="add_subtract_2",
        function_owner=self,
        position=pos2,
        rotation=rot,
        height=h,
        width=w,
        font_size=f_size,
        scale={x=3, y=3, z=3},
        font_color=f_color, 
        color = bg_color
    })
	
end

function add_subtract(_obj, _color, alt_click)
  mod = alt_click and -1 or 1
  new_value = math.min(math.max(value1 + mod, MIN_VALUE), MAX_VALUE)
  if value1 ~= new_value then
    value1 = new_value
    updateDisplay(value1, 0)
    updateSave()
  end
end

function add_subtract_2(_obj, _color, alt_click)
    mod = alt_click and -1 or 1
    new_value = math.min(math.max(value2 + mod, MIN_VALUE), MAX_VALUE)
    if value2 ~= new_value then
      value2 = new_value
      updateDisplay(value2, 1)
      updateSave()
    end
  end

function updateDisplay(value, index)
  	self.editButton({index = index, label = tostring(value)})
end

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Model
ContainedObjects.LuaScript:
local side , text , plr = '' , '' , 'Black'
local timesRolled , randomized = 0 , false

function onObjectRandomize( Object , player_color )
 if Object.getGUID() == self.getGUID() then
  if player_color ~= plr then
   changePlayer(player_color)
  end
  if not randomized then
   randomized = true
   startLuaCoroutine(self, 'whileDrop')
  end
 end
end

function whileDrop()
 while not self.resting do
  coroutine.yield(0) -- Always yield 0 to resume
 end
 randomized = false
 printDiceFace()
 coroutine.yield(1) -- Yield anything other than 0 to break out
end

function printDiceFace()
 local value = self.getValue()
 --You can customize the message per Value
 if value == 1 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got tails!'
 elseif value == 2 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got heads!'
 else
 --Or Remove the If block to make a generic message about what value they rolled
  side = ' made noise in corridor '..value
 end
 text = plr..side
 printToAll(text, self.getColorTint())
 --For if you need to know how many times a player has rolled the dice (optional)
 timesRolled = timesRolled + 1
end

function changePlayer(new)
 plr = new
 timesRolled = 0
 --This changes the color of the Dice to whom ever rolled it
 local rgb = stringColorToRGB(plr)
 local color = {rgb["r"], rgb["g"], rgb["b"]}
end

MIN_VALUE = 0
MAX_VALUE = 99

function updateSave()
    local data_to_save = {value1, value2}
    saved_data = JSON.encode(data_to_save)
    self.script_state = saved_data
end


function onLoad(saved_data)
    if saved_data ~= "" then
        local loaded_data = JSON.decode(saved_data)
        --Set up information off of loaded_data
        value1 = loaded_data[1]
        value2 = loaded_data[2]
    else
        --Set up information for if there is no saved saved data
        value1 = 0
        value2 = 0
    end

    createBtns()
end


--Beginning Setup


--Make setup button
function createBtns()
	local pos = {-0.7,0.1,0}
    local pos2 = {1.4,0.1,0}    -- position à ajuster
	local rot = {0,0,0}
	local h = 250
	local w = 250
	local f_size = 150
	local f_color = {1,1,1,255}
	local bg_color = {0,0,0,0}
	local diff = 0.8
	
	--center display
	self.createButton({
        label=tostring(value1),
        click_function="add_subtract",
        function_owner=self,
        position=pos,
        rotation=rot,
        height=h,
        width=w,
        font_size=f_size,
        scale={x=3, y=3, z=3},
        font_color = f_color,
        color = bg_color
    })

    --second display
	self.createButton({
        label=tostring(value2),
        click_function="add_subtract_2",
        function_owner=self,
        position=pos2,
        rotation=rot,
        height=h,
        width=w,
        font_size=f_size,
        scale={x=3, y=3, z=3},
        font_color=f_color, 
        color = bg_color
    })
	
end

function add_subtract(_obj, _color, alt_click)
  mod = alt_click and -1 or 1
  new_value = math.min(math.max(value1 + mod, MIN_VALUE), MAX_VALUE)
  if value1 ~= new_value then
    value1 = new_value
    updateDisplay(value1, 0)
    updateSave()
  end
end

function add_subtract_2(_obj, _color, alt_click)
    mod = alt_click and -1 or 1
    new_value = math.min(math.max(value2 + mod, MIN_VALUE), MAX_VALUE)
    if value2 ~= new_value then
      value2 = new_value
      updateDisplay(value2, 1)
      updateSave()
    end
  end

function updateDisplay(value, index)
  	self.editButton({index = index, label = tostring(value)})
end

ContainedObjects.LuaScript:
local side , text , plr = '' , '' , 'Black'
local timesRolled , randomized = 0 , false

function onObjectRandomize( Object , player_color )
 if Object.getGUID() == self.getGUID() then
  if player_color ~= plr then
   changePlayer(player_color)
  end
  if not randomized then
   randomized = true
   startLuaCoroutine(self, 'whileDrop')
  end
 end
end

function whileDrop()
 while not self.resting do
  coroutine.yield(0) -- Always yield 0 to resume
 end
 randomized = false
 printDiceFace()
 coroutine.yield(1) -- Yield anything other than 0 to break out
end

function printDiceFace()
 local value = self.getValue()
 --You can customize the message per Value
 if value == 1 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got tails!'
 elseif value == 2 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got heads!'
 else
 --Or Remove the If block to make a generic message about what value they rolled
  side = ' made noise in corridor '..value
 end
 text = plr..side
 printToAll(text, self.getColorTint())
 --For if you need to know how many times a player has rolled the dice (optional)
 timesRolled = timesRolled + 1
end

function changePlayer(new)
 plr = new
 timesRolled = 0
 --This changes the color of the Dice to whom ever rolled it
 local rgb = stringColorToRGB(plr)
 local color = {rgb["r"], rgb["g"], rgb["b"]}
end

local side , text , plr = '' , '' , 'Black'
local timesRolled , randomized = 0 , false

function onObjectRandomize( Object , player_color )
 if Object.getGUID() == self.getGUID() then
  if player_color ~= plr then
   changePlayer(player_color)
  end
  if not randomized then
   randomized = true
   startLuaCoroutine(self, 'whileDrop')
  end
 end
end

function whileDrop()
 while not self.resting do
  coroutine.yield(0) -- Always yield 0 to resume
 end
 randomized = false
 printDiceFace()
 coroutine.yield(1) -- Yield anything other than 0 to break out
end

function printDiceFace()
 local value = self.getValue()
 --You can customize the message per Value
 if value == 1 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got tails!'
 elseif value == 2 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got heads!'
 else
 --Or Remove the If block to make a generic message about what value they rolled
  side = ' made noise in corridor '..value
 end
 text = plr..side
 printToAll(text, self.getColorTint())
 --For if you need to know how many times a player has rolled the dice (optional)
 timesRolled = timesRolled + 1
end

function changePlayer(new)
 plr = new
 timesRolled = 0
 --This changes the color of the Dice to whom ever rolled it
 local rgb = stringColorToRGB(plr)
 local color = {rgb["r"], rgb["g"], rgb["b"]}
end

MIN_VALUE = 0
MAX_VALUE = 99

function updateSave()
    local data_to_save = {value1, value2}
    saved_data = JSON.encode(data_to_save)
    self.script_state = saved_data
end


function onLoad(saved_data)
    if saved_data ~= "" then
        local loaded_data = JSON.decode(saved_data)
        --Set up information off of loaded_data
        value1 = loaded_data[1]
        value2 = loaded_data[2]
    else
        --Set up information for if there is no saved saved data
        value1 = 0
        value2 = 0
    end

    createBtns()
end


--Beginning Setup


--Make setup button
function createBtns()
	local pos = {-0.7,0.1,0}
    local pos2 = {1.4,0.1,0}    -- position à ajuster
	local rot = {0,0,0}
	local h = 250
	local w = 250
	local f_size = 150
	local f_color = {1,1,1,255}
	local bg_color = {0,0,0,0}
	local diff = 0.8
	
	--center display
	self.createButton({
        label=tostring(value1),
        click_function="add_subtract",
        function_owner=self,
        position=pos,
        rotation=rot,
        height=h,
        width=w,
        font_size=f_size,
        scale={x=3, y=3, z=3},
        font_color = f_color,
        color = bg_color
    })

    --second display
	self.createButton({
        label=tostring(value2),
        click_function="add_subtract_2",
        function_owner=self,
        position=pos2,
        rotation=rot,
        height=h,
        width=w,
        font_size=f_size,
        scale={x=3, y=3, z=3},
        font_color=f_color, 
        color = bg_color
    })
	
end

function add_subtract(_obj, _color, alt_click)
  mod = alt_click and -1 or 1
  new_value = math.min(math.max(value1 + mod, MIN_VALUE), MAX_VALUE)
  if value1 ~= new_value then
    value1 = new_value
    updateDisplay(value1, 0)
    updateSave()
  end
end

function add_subtract_2(_obj, _color, alt_click)
    mod = alt_click and -1 or 1
    new_value = math.min(math.max(value2 + mod, MIN_VALUE), MAX_VALUE)
    if value2 ~= new_value then
      value2 = new_value
      updateDisplay(value2, 1)
      updateSave()
    end
  end

function updateDisplay(value, index)
  	self.editButton({index = index, label = tostring(value)})
end

ContainedObjects.LuaScript:
local side , text , plr = '' , '' , 'Black'
local timesRolled , randomized = 0 , false

function onObjectRandomize( Object , player_color )
 if Object.getGUID() == self.getGUID() then
  if player_color ~= plr then
   changePlayer(player_color)
  end
  if not randomized then
   randomized = true
   startLuaCoroutine(self, 'whileDrop')
  end
 end
end

function whileDrop()
 while not self.resting do
  coroutine.yield(0) -- Always yield 0 to resume
 end
 randomized = false
 printDiceFace()
 coroutine.yield(1) -- Yield anything other than 0 to break out
end

function printDiceFace()
 local value = self.getValue()
 --You can customize the message per Value
 if value == 1 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got tails!'
 elseif value == 2 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got heads!'
 else
 --Or Remove the If block to make a generic message about what value they rolled
  side = ' made noise in corridor '..value
 end
 text = plr..side
 printToAll(text, self.getColorTint())
 --For if you need to know how many times a player has rolled the dice (optional)
 timesRolled = timesRolled + 1
end

function changePlayer(new)
 plr = new
 timesRolled = 0
 --This changes the color of the Dice to whom ever rolled it
 local rgb = stringColorToRGB(plr)
 local color = {rgb["r"], rgb["g"], rgb["b"]}
end

ContainedObjects.LuaScript:
local side , text , plr = '' , '' , 'Black'
local timesRolled , randomized = 0 , false

function onObjectRandomize( Object , player_color )
 if Object.getGUID() == self.getGUID() then
  if player_color ~= plr then
   changePlayer(player_color)
  end
  if not randomized then
   randomized = true
   startLuaCoroutine(self, 'whileDrop')
  end
 end
end

function whileDrop()
 while not self.resting do
  coroutine.yield(0) -- Always yield 0 to resume
 end
 randomized = false
 printDiceFace()
 coroutine.yield(1) -- Yield anything other than 0 to break out
end

function printDiceFace()
 local value = self.getValue()
 --You can customize the message per Value
 if value == 1 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got tails!'
 elseif value == 2 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got heads!'
 else
 --Or Remove the If block to make a generic message about what value they rolled
  side = ' made noise in corridor '..value
 end
 text = plr..side
 printToAll(text, self.getColorTint())
 --For if you need to know how many times a player has rolled the dice (optional)
 timesRolled = timesRolled + 1
end

function changePlayer(new)
 plr = new
 timesRolled = 0
 --This changes the color of the Dice to whom ever rolled it
 local rgb = stringColorToRGB(plr)
 local color = {rgb["r"], rgb["g"], rgb["b"]}
end

ContainedObjects.LuaScript:
MIN_VALUE = 0
MAX_VALUE = 99

function updateSave()
    local data_to_save = {value1, value2}
    saved_data = JSON.encode(data_to_save)
    self.script_state = saved_data
end


function onLoad(saved_data)
    if saved_data ~= "" then
        local loaded_data = JSON.decode(saved_data)
        --Set up information off of loaded_data
        value1 = loaded_data[1]
        value2 = loaded_data[2]
    else
        --Set up information for if there is no saved saved data
        value1 = 0
        value2 = 0
    end

    createBtns()
end


--Beginning Setup


--Make setup button
function createBtns()
	local pos = {-0.7,0.1,0}
    local pos2 = {1.4,0.1,0}    -- position à ajuster
	local rot = {0,0,0}
	local h = 250
	local w = 250
	local f_size = 150
	local f_color = {1,1,1,255}
	local bg_color = {0,0,0,0}
	local diff = 0.8
	
	--center display
	self.createButton({
        label=tostring(value1),
        click_function="add_subtract",
        function_owner=self,
        position=pos,
        rotation=rot,
        height=h,
        width=w,
        font_size=f_size,
        scale={x=3, y=3, z=3},
        font_color = f_color,
        color = bg_color
    })

    --second display
	self.createButton({
        label=tostring(value2),
        click_function="add_subtract_2",
        function_owner=self,
        position=pos2,
        rotation=rot,
        height=h,
        width=w,
        font_size=f_size,
        scale={x=3, y=3, z=3},
        font_color=f_color, 
        color = bg_color
    })
	
end

function add_subtract(_obj, _color, alt_click)
  mod = alt_click and -1 or 1
  new_value = math.min(math.max(value1 + mod, MIN_VALUE), MAX_VALUE)
  if value1 ~= new_value then
    value1 = new_value
    updateDisplay(value1, 0)
    updateSave()
  end
end

function add_subtract_2(_obj, _color, alt_click)
    mod = alt_click and -1 or 1
    new_value = math.min(math.max(value2 + mod, MIN_VALUE), MAX_VALUE)
    if value2 ~= new_value then
      value2 = new_value
      updateDisplay(value2, 1)
      updateSave()
    end

local side , text , plr = '' , '' , 'Black'
local timesRolled , randomized = 0 , false

function onObjectRandomize( Object , player_color )
 if Object.getGUID() == self.getGUID() then
  if player_color ~= plr then
   changePlayer(player_color)
  end
  if not randomized then
   randomized = true
   startLuaCoroutine(self, 'whileDrop')
  end
 end
end

function whileDrop()
 while not self.resting do
  coroutine.yield(0) -- Always yield 0 to resume
 end
 randomized = false
 printDiceFace()
 coroutine.yield(1) -- Yield anything other than 0 to break out
end

function printDiceFace()
 local value = self.getValue()
 --You can customize the message per Value
 if value == 1 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got tails!'
 elseif value == 2 then
  side = ' flipped the coin and got heads!'
 else
 --Or Remove the If block to make a generic message about what value they rolled
  side = ' made noise in corridor '..value
 end
 text = plr..side
 printToAll(text, self.getColorTint())
 --For if you need to know how many times a player has rolled the dice (optional)
 timesRolled = timesRolled + 1
end

function changePlayer(new)
 plr = new
 timesRolled = 0
 --This changes the color of the Dice to whom ever rolled it
 local rgb = stringColorToRGB(plr)
 local color = {rgb["r"], rgb["g"], rgb["b"]}
end
